  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promote Good Community Policing Practices for Border Communities and Security Officials From Senegal to Benin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of the program is the promotion of good practices across the region on community-oriented policing, by strengthening institution/population relationship and encouraging community engagement. The program objectives are to raise the awareness of border communities on security related matters, to encourage their inclusion in the national border security framework; promote a more coherent approach to border security and management through improved communication, cooperation and coordination between border communities and border authorities; and strengthen the national social capital in responding to a security and humanitarian border crisis. The Senegal component of the program will be mainly continuing the implementation of the activities initiated in a previous project on community engagement. The Benin component will be considered a pilot phase to assess the willingness and interest of the administrative and security authorities of Benin to include the communities in their institutional security framework.</narrative>
  </description>
